<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Eric Tachibana's Job Preferences Description</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "FFFFFF" TEXT = "000000">

<BLOCKQUOTE>

To whom it may concern:

<P>

Thank you very much for taking the time to review my resume.  I hope the 
following information will help you get a better idea of what type of 
position I am looking for.

<P>

I hope to design, develop and maintain Full Service Corporate Intranets.
In my mind, such a position would involve any or all of three activities.

<UL>

<LI>Defining Requirements - Helping companies understand how the new
        medium can be used to address their unique needs would involve
        oversight of web site design and organization and help with the
        translation to and development of web-centered content.
	<P>
        (I feel that my technology-focussed liberal arts education and
        years as a webmaster gives me a unique perspective and intuition
        of the medium and how to make it work for diverse companies.)

<P>

 <LI>Applications Development - Designing mass customized applications
        from a strong library for multiple companies would blend multimedia
        GUI design with a strong structured and object-oriented interactive
        applications back-end.
	<P>
        (I hope to combine my experience with HTML and multimedia design,
        traditional C and Perl CGI, SQL and Java to create custom
        web-based/groupware applications for the unique needs of companies
        online. My work to this point has gained me several net awards, two
        book contracts (MIS Press and WAITE) and recognition in the press 
	(Web Week, Science)).

<P>

<LI>Maintenance - Ongoing support for clients would keep companies
        up-to-date as their needs and the available technology evolves.
        It would also maintain a continuing value-added relationship.
</UL>

What I seek in a work environment is an energetic, even frenzied,
atmosphere.  For myself, such an environment is fertile soil for my own
rapid and continual education and for the development of cutting-edge
products and services that I can be proud of. 

<P> 

Specifically, I seek a young, mid-sized company in a high-growth period
with a very strong product line, a fantastic corporate philosophy, and the
ability to leverage its product lines into ongoing value-added
relationships with clients.

<P>

Ideally, I would like to work in Asia.  I feel that the Asian market will
be "the"  most important market for companies over the next 50 years.  I
am positive that Asian expansion is going to be powerful, rapid and
exciting.  I wish to be in the heart of that transition. 

<P>

Thank you very much for your consideration.

<P>
Sincerely,
<P>
Eric Tachibana (aka Selena Sol)
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
