<html>
<head>
<title>The Ethics of Marty Rimm and CMU</title>
<!-- Changed by: Declan B. McCullagh, 17-Jan-1996 -->
</head><body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>

<p><center><a href="http://www.cmu.edu/cgi-bin/ft_http/DB=/registrar/db/fultext/course?DOC=0001226&ESN=F"><img src="graphics/hhh.high.jpg" alt="How Carnegie Mellon Helped, Hyped,
and Hosed Marty Rimm" border=0></a></center>

<center><p><a href="asst/cmu_center_for_advancement_of_applied_ethics.info><IMG
SRC="graphics/bigmaze.blue.jpg" width=400 height=287 border=0
align=center></a></center>

<center><h1>Moral Mazes</h1></center>
<center><font size=-1><i>By Declan McCullagh</i></font></center>

<blockquote>

<b>February 15, 1996:</b> The U.S. Government <a
href="http://fight-censorship.dementia.org/fight-censorship/dl?thread=DoJ+cites,+appends+Rimm+study+in+ACLU+case+reply&after=1203">
attaches Rimm's study</a> as an exhibit in its reply to the ACLU/EFF court
challenge of the Communications Decency Act.

<p><b>February 20, 1996:</b> Carnegie Mellon University top
administrators <a
href="http://fight-censorship.dementia.org/fight-censorship/dl?thread=CMU+basks+in+favorable+publicity+from+Rimm+study,+Usenet+censorship&after=1323">
bask in favorable publicity</a> from Rimm study and Usenet
censorship.

<p><b>March 1, 1996:</b> Carnegie Mellon University is expected to
report the results of the Committee of Investigation's ethics inquiry
into Rimm's research by summer 1996.

<p><b>March 10, 1996:</b> Carnegie Mellon University administrators
and Marvin Sirbu duck interview requests by journalists writing
followups. Rimm responds by saying his "83.5 percent figure is
rock solid" and that he is a victim of a "witch hunt."

<p><b>April 24, 1996:</b> <i>Boardwatch</i> article says <a href="http://fight-censorship.dementia.org/fight-censorship/dl?thread=New+CMU+study+on+net-terrorism/hate+speech,+Rimm's+acquittal?&after=2271">Rimm was acquitted</a> by CMU's Committee of Investigation.

<p><b>April 28, 1996:</b> The ACLJ, a theocratic right legal group, <a href="http://fight-censorship.dementia.org/fight-censorship/dl?thread=ACLJ+defends+CDA,+cites+Rimm+study,+TIME+article+in+law+journal&after=2328">uncritically cites Rimm study</a> as evidence of "smutty sex and scatologica" and justification for CDA.

</blockquote>

<blockquote><blockquote>
<p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="toc.html"><font size=+2><i><b>Table of Contents</i></b></a>
</font>
<blockquote>
<p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="rimm.html"><font size=+1><i>Marty Rimm</i></a>: The development
and defense of a fraudulent pornography study.</font>

<font size=+1><p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="sirbu.html"><i>Marvin Sirbu</i></a>: How a senior faculty
member became involved in a fraudulent study -- and
ignored its faults.<br></font>

<font size=+1><p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="time.html"><i>TIME Magazine</i></a>: How the nation's leading
newsweekly bought into a bogus study, featured it as a cover
story, and refused to admit it was suckered.</font>

<font size=+1><p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="cmu.html"><i>Carnegie Mellon University</i></a>: How one of the
world's top research universities was led astray by their own appetite
for cheap publicity.</font>

<font size=+1><p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
href="ref.html"><i>Index</i></a>

</blockquote>
<font size=+1><p><img src="graphics/dark.blue-ball.gif" alt="*"> <a
