<h1><img src="/pub/Graphics/Icons/eff3d_white_icon.gif" ALT="">
<a name="top">EFF &quot;Information Infrastructure - NREN &amp; NSFNet&quot; Archive</a></h1>

<H5>http://www.eff.org/pub/GII_NII/NREN_NSFNET/
</H5>



<h6>Last Updated Wed Sep 18 14:50:24 PDT 1996</h6><br>
<TABLE BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><A HREF="#files">Files</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#dirs">Subdirectories</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#onsite">On-Site Links</A></TD><h6></h6>
<TD><A HREF="#offsite">Off-Site Links</A></TD>
</TR></TABLE>


<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="boucher_nren_net92.speech"><B>boucher_nren_net92.speech</B></a>
<DD>March 1992 Remarks of Congressman Fred Boucher
    (D-VA) before the National Net '92 Conference.
<DT><a href="cisler_nren.report"><B>cisler_nren.report</B></a>
<DD>Presentations by Steve Cisler (Apple) in 1990
    regarding NREN.
<DT><a href="educom_nsf_nren_rfp.comments"><B>educom_nsf_nren_rfp.comments</B></a>
<DD>July 1992 Comments of EDUCOM Networking and
    Telecommunications Task Force on National Science Foundation Draft
    Solicitation for NSFNET
<DT><a href="fcc_nii_kapor_eff_050191.testimony"><B>fcc_nii_kapor_eff_050191.testimony</B></a>
<DD>Mitchell Kapor's testimony for the 
    FCC hearing &quot;Networks of the Future.&quot; Kapor stresses the importance of 
    designing the NPN as a platform, in order to allow independant companies 
    to develop applications, and the importance of designing the NPN in 
    such a way that it is easy for a beginner to use.
<DT><a href="harvard_nren_conf_cisler.summary"><B>harvard_nren_conf_cisler.summary</B></a>
<DD>Presentations by Steve Cisler (Apple)
    in 1990 regarding NREN.
<DT><a href="hpcci_cspp_91.report"><B>hpcci_cspp_91.report</B></a>
<DD>December 1991 report by the Computer Systems Policy
    Project &quot;Expanding the Vision of High Performance Computing and
    Communications: Linking America for the Future&quot; discussing the
    history, goals and futures of HPCCI including recommendations by the
    project.
<DT><a href="library_nren.papers"><B>library_nren.papers</B></a>
<DD>This file contains the text of six short pieces and
    a longer discussion paper prepared for the American Library
    Association confernce in June 1990. They include perspectives from
    different types of libraries: 1.&quot;Developing the Information
    Superhighway&quot; by Edwin Brownrigg 2.&quot;A Public Library Perspective&quot; by
    Lois Kershner 3.&quot;The National Research and Education Network For
    Special Libraries&quot; by Steve Cisler 4.&quot;Electronic Networking at
    Davis Senior High School&quot; by Janet Meizel 5.&quot;Free-neting&quot; by T.M.
    Grundner 6.&quot;Electronic Networking for California State and Public
    Libraries&quot; by Gary Strong, Kathy Hudson, and John Jewell 7. &quot;Thoughts 
    on the National Research and Education Network &quot; by Vinton Cerf.
    c. 1990
<DT><a href="nren_library_automation.paper"><B>nren_library_automation.paper</B></a>
<DD>Fall of 1989 paper &quot;Library Automation and
    the National Research Network,&quot; by Clifford A. Lynch, Director of
    the Division of Library Automation, University of California
    Office of the President discussing the history, future and
    implications of library automation.
<DT><a href="nren_npn_nii_kapor_eff.outline"><B>nren_npn_nii_kapor_eff.outline</B></a>
<DD>This is an unformatted version of the 
    overheads used at MIT's Imformation Marketplace Symposium on October 12. 
    Attendees received a copy of the Open Road paper in their conference
    materials. This document is dated. For the latest version of EFF's
    Open Platform proposal, which no longer focusses on ISDN, NPN,
    NREN, etc., see ftp.eff.org, pub/EFF/Policy/Open_Platform/op2.0 or
    later version (op2.1, etc.)
<DT><a href="nren_npn_nii_kapor_eff.rfc"><B>nren_npn_nii_kapor_eff.rfc</B></a>
<DD>Mitch Kapor's September 1991 memo &quot; Building
    The Open Road: The NREN As Test-Bed For The National Public Network&quot;
<DT><a href="nren_polly.article"><B>nren_polly.article</B></a>
<DD>Jean Armour Polly's,(Manager of Network Development and
    User Training NYSERNet, Inc.) Feb 1993 discussion &quot;NREN for All:
    Insurmountable Opportunity&quot; Discussing history, future, problems and 
    possibilities for NREN
<DT><a href="nren_privacy_cpsr.statement"><B>nren_privacy_cpsr.statement</B></a>
<DD>Marc Rotenberg's (CPSR) July 1992 statement
    before the National Commission on Libraries and Information Sciences
    (NCLIS) at the Open Forum on Library and Information Service's
    Roles in the National Research and Education Network (NREN)
<DT><a href="nsf_nren.rfp"><B>nsf_nren.rfp</B></a>
<DD>The NSF's request for comments invites proposals for one or
    more NAP Manager organizations to arrange for and oversee NAPs (as
    specified below) where the vBNS, NSPs, and other appropriate
    networks may interconnect. May 1993
<DT><a href="nsfnet_hr_sst-s_920312.testimony"><B>nsfnet_hr_sst-s_920312.testimony</B></a>
<DD>Testimonies before the House Committee 
    on Science, Space and Technology Subcommittee on Science public hearing 
    on the topic of &quot;Management of NSF Network.&quot;
<DT><a href="nsfnet_hr_sst-s_920312.testimony.ps.gz"><B>nsfnet_hr_sst-s_920312.testimony.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>PostScript version of 
    nsfnet_hr_sst-s_031293.testimony
<DT><a href="nsfnet_oral_kapor_eff_hr_031292.testimony"><B>nsfnet_oral_kapor_eff_hr_031292.testimony</B></a>
<DD>Mitchell Kapor's testimony 
    (with introduction and notes) before the House Committee on Science, 
    Space, and Technology Subcommittee on Science. Kapor talks about the 
    importance of subsidizing the network at the local level, rather than 
    subsidizing the service providers, promoting a business presence on the 
    internet, making the net accessible to all, and promoting the development 
    of networking applications to make the net an easy-to-use, valuable tool 
    for all users.
<DT><a href="nsfnet_written_kapor_eff_hr_031292.testimony"><B>nsfnet_written_kapor_eff_hr_031292.testimony</B></a>
<DD>Mitchell Kapor's testimony
    before the House Committee on Science, Space, and Technology 
    Subcommittee on Science. Kapor talks about the importance of 
    subsidizing the network at the local level, rather than subsidizing 
    the service providers, promoting a business presence on the internet, 
    making the net accessible to all, and promoting the development of 
    networking applications to make the net an easy-to-use, valuable tool
    for all users.
<DT><a href="open_road.eff"><B>open_road.eff</B></a>
<DD>Mitch Kapor's September 1991 memo &quot; Building The Open Road: 
    The NREN As Test-Bed For The National Public Network&quot;
<DT><a href="ostp_nren_congress.report"><B>ostp_nren_congress.report</B></a>
<DD>The National Research and Education Network
    Program's December 1992 Report to Congress Submitted by the Director
    Office of Science and Technology Policy in response to a requirement
    of The High Performance Computing Act of 1991 discussing 1.Purpose of 
    creating the NREN Program 2. Conceptual Architecture of NREN
    3. Management of NREN 4. Funding of NREN 5. Implementation of NREN
    6. Commercial Use of the NREN 7. Protection of intellectual property,
    privacy and security in NREN 8. NREN Constituencies and their
    concerns 9. Plans and Mechanisms to Address Significant issues
    10.Management/ Coordination of the HPCC Program
<DT><a href="ostp_nren_congress_rpt.ps.gz"><B>ostp_nren_congress_rpt.ps.gz</B></a>
<DD>The National Research and Education Network
    Program's December 1992 Report to Congress Submitted by the Director
    Office of Science and Technology Policy in response to a requirement
    of The High Performance Computing Act of 1991 discussing
    1.Purpose of the NREN Program 2. Conceptual Architecture of NREN
    3. Management of NREN 4. Funding of NREN 5. Implementation of NREN
    6. Commercial Use of the NREN 7. Protection of intellectual property,
    privacy and security in NREN 8. NREN Constituencies and their
    concerns 9. Plans and Mechanisms to Address Significant issues
    10. Management/ Coordination of the HPCC Program
<DT><a href="privatize_nren_kapor_eff_021491.paper"><B>privatize_nren_kapor_eff_021491.paper</B></a>
<DD>Mitch Kapor's (EFF) Feb 1991
    recommendations on the privatizations of NREN
<DT><a href="sterling_hstf.testimony"><B>sterling_hstf.testimony</B></a>
<DD>Testimony of Bruce Sterling, on the &quot;National
    Research and Education Network&quot; before the House
    Subcommittee on Telecommunications and Finance, Washington DC, April 29,
    1993. Excerpt: &quot;...However, it's a truism in technological
    development that no silver lining comes without its cloud.
    Today I'd like to mention two or three trifling problems
    that have come up that were not entirely obvious from the
    perspective of the early 1990s.&quot; Sterlings novel [pun intended] testimony
    is presented as the comments of a hypothetical NII worker from the 21st
    Century. This is probably the first time science fiction has been
    presented as testimony to a Congressional hearing.
</DL>

