<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="digicity_vienna.ece"><B>digicity_vienna.ece</B></a>
<DD>Press release in German, from Austrian organization
    eCE. Discusses the coming to Vienna the concept of a digital town,
    thereby providing public access to electronic networks. Moreover, the
    &quot;digital town&quot; aims at extending public services by
    providing electronic information on local political issues
    (electronic townhall), collecting cultural information
    (theaters, opera, museums, cinemas, etc.). As such, the
    &quot;digital town&quot; is far more than an ordinary BBS: it brings
    &quot;the network to the people.&quot; (Abstract in English).
<DT><a href="nm_communet.announce"><B>nm_communet.announce</B></a>
<DD>Announcement of a new listserv for the
    discussion of community networking issues in New Mexico.
</DL>

