<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="960703_efga_complaint.draft"><B>960703_efga_complaint.draft</B></a>
<DD>Draft complaint (lawsuit) by EF-Georgia to
    challenge the Georgia state &quot;Net police&quot; bill. Was included with EFGA's
    letter to the GA Atty. Gen.
<DT><a href="960703_efga_gaag.letter"><B>960703_efga_gaag.letter</B></a>
<DD>EF-Georgia letter to GA Attorney General asking for
    the AG's clarification of the new Georgia state &quot;Net police&quot; law. Included
    draft lawsuit challenging this law's constitutionality.
<DT><a href="960716_gaag_efga.response"><B>960716_gaag_efga.response</B></a>
<DD>Georgia (state) Attorney General's office 
    response to EF-Georgia's request for the AG's office to issue a 
    clarification of the GA &quot;Net police&quot; law. The request was bluntly denied.
<DT><a href="960924_aclu-ga.affidavit"><B>960924_aclu-ga.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of the American Civil Liberties 
    Union of Georgia, in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_afs.affidavit"><B>960924_afs.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of the Atlanta Freethought Society, 
    in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_aids-sp.affidavit"><B>960924_aids-sp.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of the AIDS Survival Project, in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_ava.affidavit"><B>960924_ava.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of the Atlanta Veterans Alliance,
    in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_c2.affidavit"><B>960924_c2.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Community ConneXion, in EFGA, ACLU, 
    et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_eff.affidavit"><B>960924_eff.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Shari Steele, Electronic Frontier 
    Foundation staff counsel, in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_efga.affidavit"><B>960924_efga.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Electronic Frontiers Georgia, in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_efga.brief"><B>960924_efga.brief</B></a>
<DD>Plaintiff's brief in support of motion for 
    preliminary injunction, in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_efga.complaint"><B>960924_efga.complaint</B></a>
<DD>Plaintiff's revised (improved by ACLU
    from EFGA original draft) final complaint (lawsuit) filed by ACLU, EFGA,
    EFF and many other parties against the Governor and Attorney General of
    the US state of Georgia, challenging the constitutionality of the 1996
    GA &quot;Net police&quot; law. The complaint explains that the new law is 
    unconstitutional because it threatens the free speech of Internet and 
    other online service users and providers in numerous ways, that range 
    from making it a crime to use a company's logo to link to their web site 
    (i.e. you get thrown in jail for giving someone free advertising), to 
    making it illegal to use anything but your full, real name online.
<DT><a href="960924_efga_case.announce"><B>960924_efga_case.announce</B></a>
<DD>EFGA, EFF and ACLU joint press release about
    the constitutional challenge filed Sept. 24, 1996 in Georgia (state),
    against the new GA &quot;Net police&quot; law, which threatens the free speech 
    rights on online service and Internet users and publishers.
<DT><a href="960924_kaye.affidavit"><B>960924_kaye.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of GA state Rep. Mitchell Kaye, in 
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_mirken.affidavit"><B>960924_mirken.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Bruce Mirken (journalist), in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_page_factory.affidavit"><B>960924_page_factory.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Page Factory, in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_pro_solutions.affidavit"><B>960924_pro_solutions.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Professional Solutions, in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_psre.affidavit"><B>960924_psre.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Property Systems Real Estate, in
    EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_troyer.affidavit"><B>960924_troyer.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of John Troyer (maintainer of the
    Safer Sex Page on the World Wide Web), in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="960924_wallace.affidavit"><B>960924_wallace.affidavit</B></a>
<DD>Declaration of Jonathan Wallace (attorney and 
    software entrepreneur), in EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA.
<DT><a href="parties.summary"><B>parties.summary</B></a>
<DD>Summary of parties to the EFGA, ACLU, et al. v. GA case.
</DL>

