<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40 ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="anarchy_gov_cyberspace.article"><B>anarchy_gov_cyberspace.article</B></a>
<DD>Ashish Gulhati's 1994 article &quot;Anarchy and
    Government in Cyberspace&quot; dealing with anarchic characteristics of
    cyberspace and how they apply to the real world &quot;brickspace&quot;
<DT><a href="bbs_dot_crackdown.article"><B>bbs_dot_crackdown.article</B></a>
<DD>Atul Chitnis' article &quot;Killer DoT&quot; discussing
    the Indian DOT policy which proposes to tax BBS operators with
    license fees. Analyzes the positive and negative impacts of such a
    plan concluding that it is a bad policy for Indian electronic
    freedom and liberty. c.Feb 1994
<DT><a href="dot_shots_part_deux.article"><B>dot_shots_part_deux.article</B></a>
<DD>&quot; DoT Shots, Part Deux&quot; article c.Feb 1994
    discussing the Indian DOT policy taking from and adding to
    bbs_dot_crackdown.article in this directory.
<DT><a href="e-monopoloy_threat.article"><B>e-monopoloy_threat.article</B></a>
<DD>Article discussing the threat that DOT
    monopoly on communications poses for electronic media.
<DT><a href="india_online.article"><B>india_online.article</B></a>
<DD>Arun Katiyar's article &quot;WIRING INTO THE WORLD&quot;
    discussing Indian interest in and exploration of cyberspace.
<DT><a href="notworking_networking.article"><B>notworking_networking.article</B></a>
<DD>Anil Garg's &quot;Networking or Notworking?&quot;
    article from the Times of India, August 29, 1994 discussing the
    history and present of Indian telecommunications policy.
<DT><a href="technohorror.article"><B>technohorror.article</B></a>
<DD>NARESH FERNANDES's &quot;TechnoHorror haunts BBSing
    fans&quot; article from The Times of India News Service reporting on DOT
    BBS policies.
</DL>

