<P></CENTER><BR><HR>
<BR><h2><A NAME="files">
<IMG SRC="/pub/Graphics/Icons/doc1_icon.gif" ALT=""></A>
Files in this Archive</h2>

<DL>
<DT><a href="wy_hea72_hb288.law"><B>wy_hea72_hb288.law</B></a>
<DD>state bill HB288 (passed as House enrolled act 72) 
    which passed recently. The new law orders the secretary of state to
    develop and implement a statewide electronic filing system to allow 
    records and documents required to be filed in the office of the secretary 
    of state by the public; to establish a central data base for all 
    records and documents filed electronically with the secretary of state;
    to provide security and protection of all information in the
    system and monitor the data base to ensure that unauthorized entry is not
    allowed; to prescribe a procedure for certification of the electronic
    filings by the secretary of state; and to Prescribe a key encryption 
    [sic!] or other identification procedure for any person wishing to file 
    records or other documents (&quot;as used in this section 'key encryption' 
    means a method of verifying the authenticity and authorship of 
    electronic communication through the use of algorithms or other codes.&quot;)
</DL>

