<br>markey_fields_hr3636.amend - Amendment suggested by Senator Markey to hr 3636
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.analysis - March 1994 EFF summary of the introductory
<br> markup of hr 3636, &quot;The National
<br> Communications Competition and Information
<br> Infrastructure Act of 1994.&quot;
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.announce - announcement of Markey's debut of the&quot;National
<br> Communications Competition and Information
<br> Infrastructure Act of 1993.&quot; and a brief
<br> summary of the bill as well as praising by the
<br> EFF
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.bill - Amended version of Markey-Fields bill, HR
<br> 3636, after initial markup. This is NOT the final
<br> version. For further amendmentsto this
<br> post-initial-markup Markey-Fields bill HR 3636;
<br> see hr3636.amend. Even that is not the final
<br> version. More will follow when available
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.changes - Summary of Revisions to House Bills 3636
<br> and 3626 which are designed to provide more
<br> opportunity for competition in long-distance
<br> telephone, cable television, and cellular
<br> communication services. HR 3636 would allow
<br> cable and telephone companies to compete in
<br> each other's lines of business. HR 3626 is a
<br> major antitrust reform measure and would allow
<br> the regional Bell telephone operating
<br> companies, known as Baby Bells or RBOCs, to
<br> offer long-distance services
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.mfj - MFJ Task Force's Jan 1994 summary of hr3636 
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.old - November 1993 version of HR 3636
<br>markey_fields_hr3636.summary - EFF Position Statement on and Summary of
<br> Bill HR-3636 National Communications
<br> Competition and Information Infrastructure
<br> Act of 1993 Introduced by Reps. Markey, Fields
<br> and Boucher
<br>markey_fields_hr3636_hr3626_ecc-tfs.testimony - Feb 1994 testimony of
<br> Edward Horowitz (CEO of
<br> Viacom) before the house
<br> energy and commerce's
<br> telecommunications and finance
<br> subcommittee relating to
<br> interactive video systems
<br>markey_hr3636.eff - Daniel Weitzner's March 1994 article announcing that Rep.
<br> Markey has Endorsed EFF's Open Platform Proposal
<br> through hr 3636. Briefly, EFF's Open Platform Proposal
<br> suggests policies to make voice, data and video services
<br> accessible to everyone, in the near term, and at low cost.
<br> Without a deliberate effort by government, business and
<br> individuals to build these requirements into the
<br> communications infrastructure, the free speech protections
<br> guaranteed by the Constitution will be in jeopardy
<br>markey_hr3636.statement - March 1994 news release announcing that hr 3636
<br> unanimously passed in the house telecom and finance
<br> subcommittee. It also includes a summary of the
<br> bill and Markey's March 1994 statement regarding
<br> the
<br> Information Infrastructure Act of 1993, &quot; and H.R.
<br> 3626, the &quot;Antitrust Reform Act of 1993.&quot;
<br>markey_hr3636_kapor.testimony - testimony of Mitch Kapor (EFF) before the
<br> subcommittee on telecom and finance regarding
<br> the national communications competition and
<br> information infrastructure act (HR 3636)
<br>markey_hr1305_cnid_91.bill - the TCPR bill of 1991 amending the Communications
<br> Act of 1934 to protect the rights of telephone
<br> subscribers
<br>markey_telecom_draft_91_kapor.testimony - Testimony of Mitch Kapor of the EFF
<br> before the subcommittee on telecom
<br> and finance regarding telecom
<br> infrastructure legislation and
<br> proposals In October 1991
